The paper deals with the queuing performance of wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of stochastic network calculus (cs.SY) and statistical characterization (cs.MM) in deriving measures of queuing performance. Additionally, the paper discusses interference-limited systems, which could fall under the category of physical-layer security (cs.PF).
